The paper deals with the characterization of the symbol error rate of a multi-dimensional constellation impaired by additive white Gaussian noise, which is a common problem in communication systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses wireless system performance, which suggests that it could belong to cs.COMM (Networking and Internet Architecture) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper uses mathematical tools such as completely monotone functions, which are commonly used in cs.MS (Mathematical Software) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
